Why an Elephant?
----------------

The PostgreSQL community chose the elephant as its mascot (symbol) because an elephant symbolizes:

🧠 Excellent Memory – Elephants are famous for remembering things. Databases are designed to store and retrieve data reliably.
💪 Strength – PostgreSQL can handle large amounts of data and complex applications.
🛡️ Reliability – Elephants are strong and dependable, just like PostgreSQL.
📈 Scalability – PostgreSQL can grow from small projects to enterprise-level systems.

